<title>USA: Checkpoint to provide labels to Microsoft.</title>
<headline>Checkpoint to provide labels to Microsoft.</headline>
<dateline>THOROFARE, N.J. 1996-11-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Checkpoint Systems Inc said Microsoft Corp will use its paper-thin radio frequency labels to protect Microsoft Office '97 products from theft in stores.</p>
<p>In a statement released Thursday, Checkpoint said its labels will be embedded in packaging of Microsoft Office '97, beginning with the launch in January.</p>
<p>Checkpoint Systems provides security systems for retailers, as well as radio frequency source tagging.</p>
<p>Reuters Chicago Newsdesk (312) 408-8787</p>
